# Next.js Patterns

## Agent Behavior

- **Never create reports >50 lines** without user explicitly saying "detailed" or "comprehensive"
- Focus on code changes only
- Conserve tokens by avoiding verbose explanations

## Proxy vs Middleware

Use `src/proxy.ts` (Next.js 16) instead of middleware:

```typescript
// src/proxy.ts
export default async function proxy(req: NextRequest) {
  // Proxy logic
}

export const config = {
  matcher: ['/((?!_next/static|_next/image|favicon.ico).*)'],
};
```

## Async Params/SearchParams (Next.js 15+)

```typescript
export default async function Page({
  params,
  searchParams,
}: {
  params: Promise<{ id: string }>;
  searchParams: Promise<{ q?: string }>;
}) {
  const { id } = await params;
  const { q } = await searchParams;
}
```

## Client with useSearchParams

```typescript
'use client';
import { Suspense } from 'react';

// ✅ Wrap in Suspense to avoid CSR bailout
export function SearchBar() {
  return (
    <Suspense fallback={<Skeleton />}>
      <SearchBarInner />
    </Suspense>
  );
}
```

## Hydration Safety

```typescript
// ❌ Wrong: Different on server vs client
<time>{new Date().toLocaleString()}</time>

// ✅ Correct: Client-only
'use client';
export function CurrentTime() {
  const [time, setTime] = useState<string>();
  useEffect(() => setTime(new Date().toLocaleString()), []);
  return <time suppressHydrationWarning>{time}</time>;
}
```

## Layout Tokens

Use design tokens from `globals.css`:

- **Page min-height**: `page-min-h` or `layoutTokens.pageMinH`
- **Auth form**: `auth-max-w`
- **Table columns**: `col-account`, `col-amount`, `col-actions`
- **Truncate**: `truncate-layout-sm`, `truncate-layout-md`
- **Skeletons**: `skeleton-row`, `skeleton-table`

## Metadata

```typescript
import type { Metadata } from 'next';

export const metadata: Metadata = {
  title: 'Page Title',
  description: 'Description',
};

// Dynamic
export async function generateMetadata({ params }): Promise<Metadata> {
  const { id } = await params;
  const entity = await getEntity(id);
  return { title: `${entity.name} | Module` };
}
```

## Error Handling Structure

```
app/
  error.tsx           # Segment errors
  global-error.tsx    # Root errors
  not-found.tsx       # 404
```

## Data Flow

- **Reads**: Server Components fetch via API client
- **Writes**: Server Actions with `'use server'`
- **Client state**: Minimize `'use client'` — forms/toggles only
